# Mintbase Grant Proposal

- **Project Name:** Mutable Web
- **Team Name:** Dapplets project
- **Payment Address:** NEEDS TO BE FILLED
- **[Level]:** 2

## Project Overview :page_facing_up:

Mutable Web is a decentralized, community-driven, legacy-compatible web3

### Overview

**Project description**
We have created a platform that enables the development, launch, and delivery of dApps that seamlessly run on top of any websites, embedding into the UX without having to get permission from the owners of those websites.

Any point on the web can be defined, attributed, and used as a source for a web3 action (transaction, tokenization, service delivery). We provide a tokenized persistence layer for this to be true.

We aim to target web3 projects that benefit from addressing their users from familiar UI of popular social networks (Twitter, Reddit, LinkedIn, Github, Youtube) by giving them new functionality.

Our platform provides opportunities and tools for the emergence of a large variant of network effects, and new business cases and aims to motivate the community, users, and web3 developers to become early adopters of the concept and promote it to the masses.

The two main elements of the Mutable Web are the environment for running applications - the browser extension that handles the delivery of applications to sites and the user. And the applications developed by third-party developers.

Currently, we have launched an MVP extension and are in the process of creating meaningful applications that will populate the first platform adopters and onboard app developers. We want to launch several small applications by turning some of the templates offered by Mintbase into comprehensible products and open the possibility for other developers to launch similar products on our platform.

Our plans to launch 3 apps, viz:

- NFT Sales Facilitator - a widget that any user can add to an existing social media post, allowing them to receive a commission through the Affiliation Direct program on a successful purchase.

- NFT illustrator widget - a user can "decorate" any social media post with an AI-generated image based on the content of the post with some added context.

- Alternative Feed widget - user can start a thread with comments based on the NFT contract under any social media post, setting their own rules for participation.

**Relation to NEAR Ecosystem / Integration into the Mintbase**
We use NEAR BOS at the very core of our project. The extension is a customized BOS-vm that allows you to download BOS components and embed them anywhere on an already existing page enriching it with web3 functionality.

Also running a separate fork of Near.Social that provides the same functionality on top of a site built entirely on BOS.
We also delivered the tool to create verifiable mappings between web2 accounts and NEAR addresses to bring new users into the ecosystem.

In using Mintbase, we see great potential to create small but useful applications that will add new NFT-based functionality to users in their usual habitats (Twitter, Reddit, YouTube, LinkedIn, and Github).

**Team's Interest in the Project**
The team's efforts are now fully focused on getting the first users and creating positive traction within the NEAR ecosystem to become one of the key projects giving BOS meaning to a wide audience of users and developers.
To achieve this goal and test our hypotheses, we participated in 4 NEAR hackathons and won 1st prizes in each of them, as well as passed the accelerator organized by Encode and Near Horizon

