### Ecosystem Fit

**Where and how does your project fit into the ecosystem?**
We believe that our solution will lead to the following results:

It will be several full-fledged applications utilizing Mintbase that will allow users to get new, previously unavailable functionality and get acquainted with the new concept of Mutable Web. We will use the marketing resources available to us to publicize these applications within the NEAR ecosystem and organize the onboarding of new users outside the system. BOS will be used as the front end of applications, so there will be a set of components that will create new patterns of using Mintbase API and based on which you can run your applications within the social networks we support.

The idea of the whole project is to enable the development of applications based on a new distribution principle, and we believe that Mintbase should be one of the main technologies that are responsible for the creation, processing, and storage of tokenized data and we want to simplify the use of technology to remove the friction from developers.

**Who is your target audience?**
Our main focus is on blockchain developers, specifically those engaged in the NEAR ecosystem, mostly developers creating decentralized applications. In addition, we plan to target the broader blockchain community as well, to whom we want to provide a meaningful new way to bring their functionality to users in new places using BOS.

**What need(s) does your project meet?**
At the global level, the project aims to address the problem of centralized ownership of websites, which leads to the loss of user control over their content, its use, and monetization, as well as the inability to influence the direction of the centralized project in any meaningful way.

At the developer level, we solve the issue of access to new, previously inaccessible audiences and solve their problems, which previously could only be handled by website owners.

**Are there any similar projects in the Mintbase / NEAR ecosystem?**
As far as we know, there is no project solving similar problems within the NEAR ecosystem.

**If not, are there similar projects in related ecosystems?**
A project that can be said to occupy a similar domain is Mask Network, but they only provide the functionality of the Twitter website and do not allow third-party developers to launch an expanded set of available applications.

