## Future Plans

We just launched a new version of our extension that uses NEAR BOS instead of predefined elements to define the UI. Since our platform is community and developer-oriented, our main focus at the moment is onboarding existing projects to use the technology, allowing them to bring their functionality to places where it wasn't possible before. We are currently in talks with several projects in the NEAR ecosystem, but since the project and BOS we are using chain agnostic we are also looking to attract projects mainly focused on social networks in other networks.
We are also working closely with Learn Near Club and will be running a series of beta tests on all released apps.
Our goal is to create a tool for managing Mutations based on DAO, which defines the list of applications available to users and the principles of revenue sharing between all participants in the process. At this stage, we want to present the project to the communities. Having launched and tested this tool we plan to launch tokenomics.


